The Global Medical Device Packaging Market is segmented based on material, pack type, application, and end-user. In terms of material, the market is categorized into plastic, paper & paperboard, glass, and others. Plastic is the most commonly used material due to its durability and flexibility. By pack type, the market is divided into trays, pouches, clamshell packs, and boxes. Trays are extensively used for packaging medical devices as they offer protection during transportation and storage. In terms of application, the market includes medical equipment, implants, diagnostic products, syringes & needles, among others. The end-user segment comprises medical device manufacturing companies, hospitals & clinics, ambulatory surgical centers, and others.

